{
  "stem": "18470.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 415.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because, at that time in Israel, there was tremendous-- it was called [HEBREW], time of great, great shortages, where people would get two eggs a week.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Milk would be measured out by-- and I saw this-- by the ladle out of cans in the streets into cups for children only.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There seemed to be enough bread and an endless amount of eggplant, which you can prepare in every which way.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I can't look an eggplant in the face to this day.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we-- we ate our way through Palestine, and I lost 30 pounds in those eight months.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Worked in kibbutzim.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One was Netzer Sereni, which was composed of Holocaust survivors.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At the end of the time, Stanley and I thought we had cleaned every chicken coop in Israel.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because when you go to a kibbutz to earn your way through, they say, what work can you do, what-- what can I do, or would like to do?",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They send you to the chicken coop.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So finally when you complain about you've-- you've already shoveled enough of that stuff, they say, OK.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "At Netzer Sereni, they needed a barn painted inside and outside.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Well, the outside was easy.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The inside, I looked inside and I said, my god, there are 300-pound sacks in there of grain.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And you had to move them from one side of the barn while you painted, and then you picked them up and move them to the other side of the barn.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This is mind-numbing stuff.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I came to Israel to be, you know, enthralled.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we left the kibbutzim, and with whatever little money we had, we began to tramp the country, hitchhike.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I almost died on the road on Tisha B'av on the ninth of Av.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
